    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-09-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-09-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="337"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d337">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.515 Silver/26</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Chinese Legation</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <p>Mr. H. H. Kung, Chinese Minister of Finance, has telegraphed to the Chinese
                    Minister denying that China has placed an embargo on silver.</p>
                <p>The recent order issued was intended to curb speculation in exchange and gold bar
                    and it should not be misinterpreted as in any way connected with the free
                    movement of silver.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-09-28">September 28,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
